==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Galilee
<hw>Gal"i*lee</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Supposed to have
been so termed in allusion to the scriptural ⟦ldquo⟧Galilee of the
Gentiles.⟦rdquo⟧ cf. OF. <ets>galil⟦eacute⟧e</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A porch or waiting room, usually at the west end
of an abbey church, where the monks collected on returning from
processions, where bodies were laid previous to interment, and where
women were allowed to see the monks to whom they were related, or to
hear divine service. Also, frequently applied to the porch of a church,
as at Ely and Durham cathedrals.</def> <rj><au>Gwilt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Galimatias</ent>⟦br⟧
